  "prompt": "Why are people so obsessed with Marilyn Monroe?",
  "response": "People are fascinated with Marilyn Monroe for several reasons:\n\n1. Iconic beauty and glamour\n- She embodied the ideal of Hollywood beauty in the 1950s\n- Known for her distinctive blonde hair and photogenic looks\n\n2. Cultural significance\n- Symbolized sexuality and femininity during a conservative era\n- Represented a major shift in perceptions of women's sexuality\n\n3. Complex personal life\n- Troubled childhood and multiple marriages\n- Struggles with mental health and substance abuse\n- Her mysterious death continues to spark speculation\n\n4. Hollywood legend status\n- Starred in famous films like \"Some Like It Hot\" and \"Gentlemen Prefer Blondes\"\n- Worked with renowned directors and actors\n- Became a global pop culture icon\n\n5. Tragic narrative\n- Her life story of rising from poverty to stardom\n- Short but impactful career\n- Untimely and controversial death at age 36\n\n6. Enduring mystique\n- Continues to represent an idealized version of mid-20th century glamour\n- Her image remains recognizable worldwide\n- Inspiration for art, fashion, and popular culture\n\nHer combination of beauty, talent, vulnerability, and tragic life story continues to captivate people decades after her death.",
